# Default search scope is CURRENT CANONICAL knowledge only.
# archive/ = superseded notes (history, searched only when explicitly asked)
# vault/   = encrypted sensitive notes (never in default search)
# journal/ = dated observations, opt-in (rg --no-ignore knowledge/journal/,
#            or bin/brain search --scope all)
# inbox/   = provisional captures awaiting consolidation, opt-in the same way.
#            Excluded so generous capture can never degrade retrieval; lint and
#            gitleaks still scan it (they read the git index, not rg).
knowledge/archive/
knowledge/vault/
knowledge/journal/
knowledge/inbox/
